INSERT INTO `core_ipo` VALUES (1,'Emiac Technologies','2026-03-27','2026-04-08','About Emiac Technologies\r\nEmiac Technologies Limited is an AI-based technology and digital solutions company that provides digital marketing and related services to businesses. The company offers a wide range of services, including content creation, branding and online reputation management, digital marketing, technical services and business automation. It serves as a one-stop partner for clients seeking digital transformation and growth, helping them improve operations, build a digital presence, and achieve their business objectives. Its offerings include developing marketing strategies, managing campaigns, creating content, and enabling automation solutions. The company serves clients across multiple sectors such as BFSI, healthcare, IT, education, and automobile. It generates revenue primarily from digital, technology-driven services, delivering tailored solutions based on client requirements and engagement outcomes.','Issue size\r\nFunds Raised in the IPO	Amount\r\nTotal issue size	31.75\r\nFresh Issue â€“ Proceeds go to the company	31.75\r\nUtilisation of proceeds\r\nPurpose	INR crores (%)\r\nPurchase of computers, laptops, accessories, software & cloud hosting	5.72 (18.02%)\r\nWorking capital requirements	8.8 (27.72%)\r\nHiring of manpower	5.42 (17.07%)\r\nBranding, advertisement & marketing\r\n3.9 (12.28%)\r\nGeneral corporate purposes	7.91 (24.91%)\r\nStrengths\r\nOffers end-to-end digital solutions including content, marketing, branding and automation services.\r\nUses AI, automation and data-driven insights to deliver tailored solutions to clients.\r\nServes diverse industries such as BFSI, healthcare, IT, education and automobile.\r\nFocuses on integrated digital strategies, including omnichannel campaigns and business automation.\r\nHolds multiple ISO certifications for quality, security and customer management systems. \r\nRisks\r\nHigh dependence on key customers for a significant portion of revenue.\r\nRevenue is largely dependent on digital marketing spend by clients, which can fluctuate.\r\nRapid technological changes may make services outdated if not continuously upgraded.\r\nIntense competition and evolving industry trends may impact client acquisition and retention.\r\nClients may shift marketing activities in-house, reducing demand for the companyâ€™s services.\r\nSubscription Figures for Emiac Technologies\r\nAccording to media reports (Link), Emiac Technologies is seeing no premium in the grey market. Since GMP is an unreliable indicator, IPO subscription data from the exchanges offers a more accurate view of market demand.\r\n\r\nSubscription numbers as of 05:00 PM on April 06, 2026:\r\n\r\nCategory	Reserved (lakhs)	Applied (lakhs)	Subscription (X times)\r\nInstitutional	6.24	6.38	1.02x\r\nNII	6.36	5.64	0.89x\r\nRetail	10.92	10.56	0.97x\r\nTotal	23.52	22.58	0.96x','WAITING','2026-04-05 12:46:02.502214','2026-04-07 08:17:57.358977'),(2,'Om Power Transmission','2026-04-09','2026-04-13','About Om Power Transmission Ltd.\r\nIncorporated in June 2011, Om Power Transmission Limited is a power transmission infrastructure engineering, procurement, and construction (EPC) company with over 14 years of experience.\r\n\r\nThe company\'s expertise lies in the execution of high-voltage (â€ś HVâ€ť) and extra-high voltage (â€śEHVâ€ť) transmission lines, substations and underground cabling projects delivered on a turnkey basis, encompassing design, engineering, supply, erection, installation, testing, commissioning, and comprehensive operation and maintenance (â€śO&Mâ€ť) services.\r\n\r\nThe company is certified under ISO 9001:2015, ISO 45001:2018, and ISO 14001:2015. \r\n\r\nAs of December 31, 2025, the unexecuted Order Book comprised 58 projects amounting to â‚ą 74,460.27 lakhs, including 51 EPC projects and 7 O&M contracts.','Om Power Transmission IPO is a book build issue of â‚ą150.06 crores. The issue is a combination of fresh issue of 0.76 crore shares aggregating to â‚ą132.56 crores and offer for sale of 0.10 crore shares aggregating to â‚ą17.50 crores.\r\n\r\nOm Power Transmission IPO opens for subscription on Apr 9, 2026 and closes on Apr 13, 2026. The allotment for the Om Power Transmission IPO is expected to be finalized on Apr 15, 2026. Om Power Transmission IPO will list on the NSE and the BSE with a tentative listing date fixed as Apr 17, 2026.\r\n\r\nOm Power Transmission IPO is set issue price band at â‚ą166 to â‚ą175 per share. The lot size for an application is 85 shares. The minimum amount of investment required by an individual investor (retail) is â‚ą14,875 (85 shares) (based on upper price). The lot size investment for sNII is 14 lots (1,190 shares), amounting to â‚ą2,08,250, and for bNII, it is 68 lots (5,780 shares), amounting to â‚ą10,11,500.\r\n\r\nBeeline Capital Advisors Pvt.Ltd. is the book running lead manager and MUFG Intime India Pvt.Ltd. is the registrar of the issue.\r\n\r\nRefer to Om Power Transmission IPO RHP  for detailed Information\r\nTotal Issue Size	85,75,000 shares\r\n(agg. up to â‚ą150 Cr)\r\nFresh Issue	75,75,000 shares\r\n(agg. up to â‚ą133 Cr)\r\nOffer for Sale	10,00,000 shares of â‚ą10\r\n(agg. up to â‚ą18 Cr)\r\nShare Holding Pre Issue	2,66,70,000 shares\r\nShare Holding Post Issue	3,42,45,000 shares','WAITING','2026-04-09 05:09:39.347243','2026-04-09 05:09:39.347313'),(3,'test','2026-04-21','2026-04-25','test','test','APPLY','2026-04-21 09:07:30.175951','2026-04-21 10:26:30.007673');
